@DrSajid I know this is a closed issue but here is what worked for me:
I was using zsh(oh-my-zsh specifically) instead of bash for my temrinal and, although the lib64 path was set for bash, it wouldn't work for zsh.
Try exec bash on terminal to switch to bash and try again.

body:
@DrSajid I know this is a closed issue but here is what worked for me:
I was using zsh(oh-my-zsh specifically) instead of bash for my temrinal and, although the lib64 path was set for bash, it wouldn't work for zsh.

Try ``exec bash`` on terminal to switch to bash and try again.
